dc_title_s: Dickinson County, Iowa, 1939, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BZL. Form of individual image numbering: BZL-1-[number], or BZL-2-[number]. Flown by Aero Service Corp. Philidelphia, Pa. Date of publication inferred from dates on individual photographs within the mosaic. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
dc_publisher_s: United States. Department of Agriculture|United States. Agricultural Stabilization and Conservation Service
